text: Kevin F. Parker (born 2 May 1943) is a former Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League (VFL). Originally from Colac, he played as a rover or back pocket == Notes == == External links == * * Category:1943 births Category:Living people Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia) Category:Sydney Swans players
